		(comment 1 "Architecture Level B: connector groups and protected testpoint classes")
		(comment 2 "No connector family, pin count, wire gauge or footprint selected")
	)
	(lib_symbols)
	(text "19_BFE_CONNECTORS_TESTPOINTS - LEVEL B GROUPS\nThis sheet collects PCB-A connector/test boundaries without selecting physical connector families.\nExternal battery power is still governed by SN-176A-12 and the separate LOCAL_START connector outside PCB-A.\nPCB-A exposes PACK_BUS fanout, control, diagnostics, EXT_KILL and protected service testpoints."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 18 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.35 1.35)) (justify left))
		(uuid "bfe-lb-00000019-0000-4000-8000-000000000101")
	)
	(text "CONNECTOR GROUP CLASSES\nPWR_OUT_GROUPS: PACK_BUS_TO_CRIT/P12/P5/LIGHT with returns sized later.\nCTRL_IN_GROUP: enable, safe-off, discharge, balance and hold-loop open commands.\nDIAG_OUT_GROUP: BFE measurements, faults and status.\nEXT_KILL_CHAIN: hardware safety path, not firmware-only."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 86 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.25 1.25)) (justify left))
		(uuid "bfe-lb-00000019-0000-4000-8000-000000000102")
	)
	(text "TESTPOINT POLICY\nTestpoints shall support bring-up, fault injection and verification without bypassing BMS, fuses or K_BAT hold-loop safety.\nHigh-current and hazardous points require guarded/protected service access.\nConnector family, pin count, shield, keying, wire section and colors remain TBD."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12 158 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.25 1.25)) (justify left))
		(uuid "bfe-lb-00000019-0000-4000-8000-000000000103")
	)
